n</i> has tended to be replaced by <i>Hardeman</i>, and elsewhere in Ireland by   Harman   and   Harmon  ."]},{"name":"Harmony","meanings":["Variant of   Harmon  , a surname of German origin.","English: unexplained. This surname is very rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Harmon was born as the son of John Harmon and Lady Collett Ayres. He had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Lady Margaret Margery Squire."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1455–1501":"1455–1501","–1508":"–1508","–Male":"Surnud","1458–1537":"1458–1537","1474–1535":"1474–1535","1477–1535":"1477–1535","1483–1533":"1483–1533","–1594":"–1594","1430–1462":"1430–1462","1432–1455":"1432–1455","1462":"1462","1594":"1594","1483":"1483","1535":"1535","1458":"1458","1501":"1501","1533":"1533","1477":"1477","1455":"1455","1432":"1432","1430":"1430","1474":"1474","1508":"1508","about 1474":"umbes 1474","1537":"1537","Crayford, Kent, England":"Crayford, Kent, England","England":"England","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1455–1501":"1455–1501","–1508":"–1508","–Male":"Kuollut","1458–1537":"1458–1537","1474–1535":"1474–1535","1477–1535":"1477–1535","1483–1533":"1483–1533","–1594":"–1594","1430–1462":"1430–1462","1432–1455"